<seg id=1> Fei Xiaotong Was Conferred the Magsaisai Prize </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Manila, August 31, Telegram (Reporter Xiong Changyi).  Dr. Fei Xiaotong, China's famous sociologist and vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, was conferred the 1994 Megsaisai "Community Leader" prize here this afternoon.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The prize issuing ceremony was solemnly held at Philippines Culture Center.  </seg>
<seg id=4> Philippines President Lamos attended the prize issuing ceremony and issued medals, money award, and certificates to six outstanding figures awarded this year's Megsaisai Prize.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> In his acknowledgement statement, Fei Xiaotong said that "I will always live up to the encouragement of the friendly neighboring country. No matter how much time I can use in the future, I will certainly make use of each every moment conscientiously and try my best to do Asian people and people of the world some good turns, making the knowledge accumulated by mankind effective in promoting the social advancement towards a better society".  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Ramon Megsaisai Prize named after the former President of the Philippines is called as the Asia Nobel Prize. </seg>
<seg id=7> The annually issued prize covers five aspects and is awarded to individuals and organizations making outstanding contributions in government service, public service, communication leader, news, literature and creative art of communication and international understanding fields.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Since the beginning of prize issuance in 1958, 172 individuals and 14 organizations have been conferred the prize.  </seg>
</p>
